                '        README.md\n'
                '      </h2>\n'
                '    </div>\n'
                '        <div class="Popover anim-scale-in '

                '\n'
                '      <div class="Box-body p-5">\n'
                '        <article class="markdown-body entry-content" '
                'itemprop="text"><h1><a id="user-content-askocli" '
                'class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#askocli"><svg '
                'class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" '
                'version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path '
                'fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 '
                '4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 '
                '1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 '
                '9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 '
                '0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 '
                '3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 '
                '6z"></path></svg></a>Askocli</h1>\n'
                '<p>AskOcli allow an <a '
                'href="https://github.com/askomics/askomics">AskOmics</a> user '
                'to integrate file with the command line into a distant <a '
                'href="https://github.com/askomics/askomics">AskOmics</a>.</p>\n'
                '<h2><a id="user-content-requirment" class="anchor" '
                'aria-hidden="true" href="#requirment"><svg class="octicon '
                'octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" '
                'height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" '
                'd="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 '
                '3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 '
                '5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 '
                '2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 '
                '0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 '
                '13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 '
                '6z"></path></svg></a>Requirment</h2>\n'
                '<ul>\n'
                '<li>python3</li>\n'
                '<li>python3-venv</li>\n'
                '</ul>\n'
                '<h2><a id="user-content-installation" class="anchor" '
                'aria-hidden="true" href="#installation"><svg class="octicon '
                'octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" '
                'height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" '
                'd="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 '
                '3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 '
                '5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 '
                '2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 '
                '0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 '
                '13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 '
                '6z"></path></svg></a>Installation</h2>\n'
                '<p>Clone the repository</p>\n'
                '<pre><code>git clone '
                'https://github.com/askomics/asko-cli.git\n'
                'cd asko-cli\n'
                '</code></pre>\n'
                '<p>Set up a virtual environment:</p>\n'
                '<pre><code>python3 -m venv venv\n'
                'source venv/bin/activate\n'
                '</code></pre>\n'
                '<p>Install the script in the virtual environment:</p>\n'
                '<pre><code>python3 setup.py install\n'
                '</code></pre>\n'
                '<h2><a id="user-content-usage-example" class="anchor" '
                'aria-hidden="true" href="#usage-example"><svg class="octicon '
                'octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" '
                'height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" '
                'd="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 '
                '3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 '
                '5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 '
                '2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 '
                '0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 '
                '13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 '
                '6z"></path></svg></a>Usage example</h2>\n'
                '<p>Integration</p>\n'
                '<pre><code>askocli integrate -a http://localhost -p 6543 -k '
                'mYap1Key path/to/file.csv\n'
                'askocli integrate -a http://localhost -p 6543 -k mYap1Key '
                'path/to/file.csv\n'
                'askocli integrate -a http://localhost -p 6543 -k mYap1Key -e '
                'gene transcript -t Arabidopsis_thaliana path/to/file.gff\n'
                'askocli integrate -a http://localhost -p 6543 -k mYap1Key '
                'path/to/file.ttl\n'
                '</code></pre>\n'
                '<h2><a id="user-content-history" class="anchor" '
                'aria-hidden="true" href="#history"><svg class="octicon '
                'octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" '
                'height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" '
                'd="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 '
                '3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 '
                '5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 '
                '2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 '
                '0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 '
                '13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 '
                '6z"></path></svg></a>History</h2>\n'
                '<ul>\n'
                '<li>0.1: Initial release!\n'
                '<ul>\n'
                '<li>Integrate CSV file into a distant AskOmics</li>\n'
                '</ul>\n'
                '</li>\n'
                '<li>0.2:\n'
                '<ul>\n'
                '<li>Use API key instead of password</li>\n'
                '<li>Integrate GFF and TTL</li>\n'
                '</ul>\n'
                '</li>\n'
                '<li>0.3: APIkey\n'
                '<ul>\n'
                '<li>Use only the API key without the username to login</li>\n'
                '<li>Better error managment</li>\n'
                '<li>Option <code>-c</code>, <code>--columns</code> to force '
                'the columns types</li>\n'
                '<li>Option <code>--key-columns</code> to set the key '
                'columns</li>\n'
                '<li>Option <code>--public</code> to integrate public '
                'data</li>\n'
                "<li>Option <code>--disabled-columns</code> to don't integrate "
                'a columns of a TSV</li>\n'
                '</ul>\n'
                '</li>\n'
                '<li>0.3.2\n'
                '<ul>\n'
                '<li>FIX error message</li>\n'
                '</ul>\n'
                '</li>\n'
                '</ul>\n'
                '</article>\n'
                '      </div>\n'
                '  </div>\n'
                '\n'

                '            var lastRow = ""\n'

                '            //if (row1[3] && row[4]){lastRow += ","}\n'
                '            if (row1[4] != ""){lastRow += "!miR"}\n'

                '                [\n'
                '                    row1[0],\n'
                '                    row1[1],\n'
                '                    row1[2],\n'
                '                    lastRow\n'
                '                ]\n'
                '            );\n'
                '        }  \n'
                '    }\n'

                '    <h2>Automatic Statistical Identification in Complex '
                'Spectra</h2>\n'
                '\n'
                '    <p>\n'
                '\tBioconductor version: Release (3.10)\n'
                '    </p>\n'
                '\n'
                '    <p>With a set of pure metabolite reference spectra, ASICS '
                'quantifies concentration of metabolites in a complex '
                'spectrum. The identification of metabolites is performed by '
                'fitting a mixture model to the spectra of the library with a '
                'sparse penalty. The method and its statistical properties are '
                'described in Tardivel et al. (2017) <doi:10.1007 '
                's11306-017-1244-5="">.</doi:10.1007></p>\n'
                '\n'
                '    <p>Author: Gaëlle Lefort [aut, cre], Rémi Servien [aut], '
                'Patrick Tardivel [aut], Nathalie Vialaneix [aut] </p>\n'
                '\n'
                '    <p>Maintainer: Gaëlle Lefort &lt;gaelle.lefort at '
                'inra.fr&gt; </p>\n'
                '\n'
                '\n'
                '   <div id="bioc_citation_outer" style="display: block;">\n'
                '    <p>Citation (from within R,\n'
                '      enter <code>citation("ASICS")</code>):</p>\n'
                '      <div id="bioc_citation" '
                'class="bioc_citation"><p>Tardivel P, Canlet C, Lefort G, '
                'Tremblay-Franco M, Debrauwer L, Concordet D, Servien R '
                '(2017).\n'
                '“ASICS: an automatic method for identification and '
                'quantification of metabolites in complex 1D 1H NMR spectra.”\n'
                '<em>Metabolomics</em>, <b>13</b>(10), 109.\n'
                '<a '
                'href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11306-017-1244-5">https://doi.org/10.1007/s11306-017-1244-5</a>. \n'
                '</p>\n'
                '</div>\n'
                '    </div>\n'

                 b'wnloads/release/ASICS.svg" title="Ranking by number of downl'
                 b'oads. A lower number means the package is downloaded more fr'
                 b'equently. Determined within a package type (software, experi'
                 b'ment, annotation, workflow) and uses the number of distinct '
                 b'IPs for the last 12 months."></a>\n      \n      </td>\n   '

                 b'8129/B9.bioc.ASICS">10.18129/B9.bioc.ASICS</a> &nbsp;\n\n<'

                 b'16" src="/images/facebook.png"></a> &nbsp;\n<a title="Sha'
                 b're on Twitter" href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=ht'
                 b'tps%3A%2F%2Fbioconductor.org%2Fpackages%2F3.10%2Fbioc%2Fhtml'

                 b'16" src="/images/twitter.png"></a>\n\n   \n\n   \n\n   \n\n '
                 b'   <h2>Automatic Statistical Identification in Complex Spect'
                 b'ra</h2>\n\n    <p>\n\tBioconductor version: Release (3.1'
                 b'0)\n    </p>\n\n    <p>With a set of pure metabolite refere'
                 b'nce spectra, ASICS quantifies concentration of metabolites i'
                 b'n a complex spectrum. The identification of metabolites is p'
                 b'erformed by fitting a mixture model to the spectra of the li'
                 b'brary with a sparse penalty. The method and its statistical '
                 b'properties are described in Tardivel et al. (2017) <doi:10.1'
                 b'007 s11306-017-1244-5="">.</doi:10.1007></p>\n\n    <p>Aut'
                 b'hor: Ga\xc3\xablle Lefort [aut, cre], R\xc3\xa9mi Servien [a'
                 b'ut], Patrick Tardivel [aut], Nathalie Vialaneix [aut] </'
                 b'p>\n\n    <p>Maintainer: Ga\xc3\xablle Lefort &lt;gaelle.lef'
                 b'ort at inra.fr&gt; </p>\n\n\n   <div id="bioc_citation_oute'
                 b'r" style="display: block;">\n    <p>Citation (from within'
                 b' R,\n      enter <code>citation("ASICS")</code>):</p>\n   '
                 b'   <div id="bioc_citation" class="bioc_citation"><p>Tardivel'
                 b' P, Canlet C, Lefort G, Tremblay-Franco M, Debrauwer L, Conc'
                 b'ordet D, Servien R (2017).\n\xe2\x80\x9cASICS: an automati'
                 b'c method for identification and quantification of metabolite'
                 b's in complex 1D 1H NMR spectra.\xe2\x80\x9d\n<em>Metabolom'
                 b'ics</em>, <b>13</b>(10), 109.\n<a href="https://doi.org/1'
                 b'0.1007/s11306-017-1244-5">https://doi.org/10.1007/s11306-017'
                 b'-1244-5</a>. \n</p>\n</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <h3>Instal'
                 b'lation</h3>\n\n    <p>To install this package, start R (ve'
                 b'rsion\n    "3.6") and enter:\n    </p>\n\n    <pre>if (!requ'
                 b'ireNamespace("BiocManager", quietly = TRUE))\n    install'
                 b'.packages("BiocManager")\n\nBiocManager::install("ASICS")<'
                 b'/pre>\n\n    <p>For older versions of R, please refer to t'
                 b'he appropriate\n\t<a href="/about/release-announcements/">'
                 b'Bioconductor release</a>.\n    </p>\n\n    <h3>Documentatio'
                 b'n</h3>\n\n\n  \n<p>To view documentation for the version of '
                 b'this package installed\n    in your system, start R and e'
                 b'nter:\n</p>\n<pre>browseVignettes("ASICS")</pre>\n    <p>&n'
                 b'bsp;</p>\n\n\n\n    <table>\n\t\n\t\n\t\n\t    \n\t\t\n\t'

{'JavaScript': 'Yes',
 'bodyContent': '<html><head>\n'
                '<title>The ASPEX package: affected sib-pair exclusion '
                'mapping</title>\n'
                '</head>\n'
                '<body>\n'
                '<h2><a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/aspex">\n'
                '<img '
                'src="http://sourceforge.net/sflogo.php?group_id=90166&amp;type=1"></a>\n'
                'The ASPEX package: affected sib-pair exclusion mapping</h2>\n'
                '<p>\n'
                'ASPEX is a set of programs for analysis of affected sibling '
                'pair data\n'
                'for discrete traits.  There are five main analysis programs:\n'
                '<code>sib_ibd</code>, <code>sib_phase</code>, '
                '<code>sib_map</code>,\n'
                '<code>sib_tdt</code>, and <code>sib_kin</code>.\n'
                '</p><ul>\n'
                '<li> <code>sib_ibd</code> performs exclusion mapping for data '
                'sets\n'
                '     with typed parents, and makes no inferences about '
                'missing data.\n'
                '</li><li> <code>sib_phase</code> performs exclusion mapping '
                'using allele\n'
                '     frequencies to reconstruct missing information, and is '
                'tailored\n'
                '     for data sets with missing parents, but additional typed '
                'children \n'
                '     that can be used to reconstruct and phase the parents.\n'
                '</li><li> <code>sib_map</code> is for multipoint marker '
                'distance estimation\n'
                '     from sib pair data.\n'
                '</li><li> <code>sib_tdt</code> is for transmission '
                'disequilibrium testing.\n'
                '</li><li> <code>sib_kin</code> is for verifying the degree of '
                'relatedness\n'
                '     of individuals within a family.\n'
                '</li></ul>\n'
                'ASPEX on-line resources include:\n'
                '<ul>\n'
                '<li>SourceForge\n'
                '<a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/aspex">project '
                'page</a>,\n'
                'with bug reporting and discussion forums\n'
                '</li><li>Source code for the\n'

                'href="http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=90166">\n'

                '</li><li>An online manual in <a href="usage.html">HTML</a>\n'
                '    and <a href="usage.pdf">PDF</a> formats\n'

                 b'center></div>\n<div id="main">\n<br><div style="width: 65e'
                 b'm"><font size="2"><b>ASPicDB</b> is a database designed to p'
                 b'rovide access to reliable annotations of the alternative spl'
                 b'icing pattern of human genes, obtained by <b>ASPic</b> algor'
                 b"ithm (<i>T. Castrignano' et al. 2006</i>) and Pintron algori"
                 b'thm (<i>Y. Pirola et al. 2012</i>), and to the functional an'
                 b'notation of predicted isoforms.<br><br>\n\t\n\tEnhanced quer'
                 b'y and download facilities allow users to select and extract '
                 b'specific sets of data related to genes, transcripts and intr'
                 b'ons fulfilling a combination of user-defined criteria. Sever'
                 b'al tabular and graphical views of the results are presented,'
                 b' providing a comprehensive assessment of the functional impl'
                 b'ication of alternative splicing in the gene set under invest'
                 b'igation.\n\tASPicDB also includes information on tissue-sp'
                 b'ecific splicing patterns of normal and cancer cells, based o'
                 b'n available EST data and their library source annotation.</f'
                 b'ont></div><br><br><br><table><tbody><tr><td> <br><font size='
